os F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n| {{flagicon|GRE}} [[Takis Lemonis]]\n| [[Piraeus]]\n| [[Olympic Stadium (Athens)|Athens Olympic Stadium]]\n| align=\"center\" | 71,030\n|-\n| [[Panachaiki F.C.|Panachaiki]] \n| {{flagicon|GRE}} [[Nikos Anastopoulos]]\n| [[Patras]]\n| [[Kostas Davourlis Stadium]]\n| align=\"center\" | 11,321\n|-\n| [[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]\n| {{flagicon|URU}} [[Sergio Markari\u00e1n]]\n| [[Athens]]\n| [[Leoforos Alexandras Stadium|Apostolos Nikolaidis Stadium]]\n| align=\"center\" | 16,620\n|-\n| [[Panionios F.C.|Panionios]] \n| {{flagicon|ROM}} [[Dumitru Dumitriu]]\n| [[Nea Smyrni]]\n| [[Nea Smyrni Stadium]]\n| align=\"center\" | 11,756\n|-\n| [[PAOK FC|PAOK]]\n| {{flagicon|BIH}} [[Du\u0161an Bajevi\u0107]]\n| [[Thessaloniki]]\n| [[Toumba Stadium]]\n| align=\"center\" | 28,803\n|-\n| [[Xanthi F.C.|Xanthi]]\n| {{flagicon|GRE}} [[Nikos Karageorgiou]]\n| [[Xanthi]]\n| [[Xanthi Ground]]\n| align=\"center\" | 9,500\n|}\n* <small><sup>1</sup> On final match day of the season, played on 8 May 2002.</small>\n\n==League standings==\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|show_limit = 5\n|res_col_header=QR\n\n|team1=OLY|name_OLY=[[Olympiacos F.C.|Olympiacos]]\n|team2=AEK|name_AEK=[[AEK Athens F.C.|AEK Athens]]\n|team3=PAT|name_PAT=[[Panathinaikos F.C.|Panathinaikos]]\n|team4=PAOK|name_PAOK=[[PAOK FC|PAOK]]\n|team5=XAN|name_XAN=[[Xanthi F.C.|Xanthi]]\n|team6=IRT|name_IRT=[[Iraklis 1908 Thessaloniki F.C.|Iraklis]]\n|team7=PIO|name_PIO=[[Panionios F.C.|Panionios]]\n|team8=OFI|name_OFI=[[OFI Crete|OFI]]\n|team9=ARI|name_ARI=[[Aris Thessaloniki F.C.|Aris]]\n|team10=EGA|name_EGA=[[Egaleo F.C.|Egaleo]]\n|team11=AKR|name_AKR=[[Akratitos F.C.|Akratitos]]\n|team12=ION|name_ION=[[Ionikos F.C.|Ionikos]]\n|team13=PCK|name_PCK=[[Panachaiki F.C.|Panachaiki]]\n|team14=ETA|name_ETA=[[Ethnikos Asteras F.C.|Ethnikos Asteras]]\n\n|win_OLY=17|draw_OLY=7|loss_OLY=2|gf_OLY=69|ga_OLY=30|status_OLY=C\n|win_AEK=19|draw_AEK=1|loss_AEK=6|gf_AEK=65|ga_AEK=28\n|win_PAT=16|d